500|$|The 1982 NFL strike {{began on}} September 21, 1982, and lasted 57 days, ending on November 16, 1982. During this time, no NFL games were played. The strike {{occurred}} because the union demanded that a <b>wage</b> <b>scale</b> based on percentage of gross revenues be implemented. The NFLPA wanted the percentage to be 55 percent, {{and according to}} the Los Angeles Times, this demand [...] "dominated the negotiations." ...|$|E
