50|$|In 1970 American Airlines had {{flights from}} St. Louis, Chicago, and New York to Honolulu {{and on to}} Sydney and Auckland via American Samoa and Nadi, Fiji. In 1971, American {{acquired}} Trans Caribbean Airways. On March 30, 1973 American became the first major airline to employ a female pilot when Bonnie Tiburzi was hired to fly Boeing 727s. American Airlines has been innovative in other aspects, initiating several of the industry's major competitive developments including computer reservations systems, frequent flyer loyalty programs, and two-tier <b>wage</b> <b>scales.</b>|$|R
